  "instruction": "Set up a new web project in the terminal: create the directories ~/Desktop/webapp/src/ and ~/Desktop/webapp/tests/, then create ~/Desktop/webapp/.gitignore with two entries '*.pyc' and '__pycache__/' (one per line), and create ~/Desktop/webapp/src/main.py containing the single line print('Hello, World!'). Configure VS Code User Settings with four changes: enable editor.bracketPairColorization.enabled, set editor.wordWrap to 'on', enable files.insertFinalNewline, and set editor.tabSize to 2. Finally, in Chrome, bookmark https://code.visualstudio.com/ to your bookmarks bar.",
